name: SCNTFC - "Guns and Roses" Invasion No.001
description: The first in the Static Invasion sticker set series features our in house designer SCNTFC’s die cut nature images. Look close and you’ll see the flowers are actually tanks and grenades…how patriotic! features four 7”x11” pages of white die cut stickers. Visit our blog to see how Guns and Roses look in use.

name: Kid Koala - "Edamame" Invasion No.003
description: You may know Kid Koala as Ninja Tune’s turntablist virtuoso, but he’s also well known for his art. Koala’s pen and ink drawing style is featured as part of many of his music releases, and now we’ve got him on board with a Static Invasion Sticker Kit. Features four 7”x11” pages of black and white die cut stickers of various sizes.

name: Steven - "F'Yeah" Invasion No.002
description: Los Angeles based artist, musician and writer Steven hit us up with an awesome collection of stickers. The kit features many of his cartoon characters, plus many word bubble sayings for you to help embellish the cartoons (or maybe other things you see on the street that need to make a statement). Kit features 2 color designs on four 7”x11” pages.

name: Jilf - "Jilflings" Invasion No.004
description: Seattle street artist Jilf has put together a kit of his lovable Jilflings. This kit features multicolor designs on four 7”x11” sheets.
